<p>Most of the raids took place in London after beginning with 'Black Saturday' on September 7, 1940, when the Luftwaffe attacked the London Docklands.</p>

<p>They would go on to bomb the capital city day and night for months, switching to night-only operations in October.</p>

<p>While the air raids mainly targeted London, where they wreaked havoc and killed thousands, they were carried out across the UK, with devastating attacks aimed at Bristol, Birmingham, Coventry, Bath, Cardiff, Clydebank, Liverpool, Manchester, Plymouth, Portsmouth, Sheffield, Southampton, Swansea and Swindon before the campaign came to an end in May 1941, seven months after it had began.</p>
